[{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"CurrentModule = QuadraticAberrationCorrector","category":"page"},{"location":"#QuadraticAberrationCorrector","page":"Home","title":"QuadraticAberrationCorrector","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Documentation for QuadraticAberrationCorrector.","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Modules = [QuadraticAberrationCorrector]","category":"page"},{"location":"#QuadraticAberrationCorrector.CorrectAberration-Tuple{Any}","page":"Home","title":"QuadraticAberrationCorrector.CorrectAberration","text":"CorrectAberration(ϕ)\n\nReturns the corrected phase map of ϕ using the least squares algorithm. Argument ϕ must be an unwrapped phase.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#QuadraticAberrationCorrector.WeightedCorrectAberration-Tuple{Any, Any, Any}","page":"Home","title":"QuadraticAberrationCorrector.WeightedCorrectAberration","text":"WeightedCorrectAberration(ϕ, ρx, ρy)\n\nReturns the corrected phase map of ϕ using the weighted least squares algorithm. Argument ρx and ρy are division numbers. The input phase map ϕ is divided into a rho_xtimesrho_y grid to obtain a weighted matrix based on the maximum-minimum-average-standard deviation (MMASD) metric. See the following reference for details.\n\nZhenkai Chen, Wenjing Zhou, Lian Duan, Hongbo Zhang, Huadong Zheng, Xinxing Xia, Yingjie Yu, and Ting-chung Poon, \"Automatic elimination of phase aberrations in digital holography based on Gaussian 1σ- criterion and histogram segmentation,\" Opt. Express 31, 13627-13639 (2023)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"}]
